<head>Personal.&#8212;</head>

<p><seg type="Source" subtype="Government">Dr. <persName key="Forney, Jacob">Forney</persName>, the Superintendent of Indian Affairs, arrived in <placeName type="settlement" key="Salt Lake City, UT">this city</placeName> from his late visit to the southern portion of <placeName type="state" key="Utah Territory">the Territory</placeName>.</seg>  <persName key="Forney, Jacob">The Doctor</persName> looks well and is in good health, and reports the Indians in that vicinity as peaceable.  <seg type="Massacre" subtype="Survivors">He brought with him three of the children, survivors of the Mountain Meadow massacre, the others as will be seen by reference to another paragraph, are at the Indian farm at <geogName type="waterway" key="Spanish Fork">the Spanish Fork</geogName>.  The children that he brought up are apparently very intelligent and have a lively recollection of <seg type="Massacre" subtype="Casualties">the bloody deeds that consigned their parents and friends to death</seg>, <seg type="Blame" subtype="LDS_LDS">if there were no other proof know the difference between an indian and a <hi rend="italic">white man</hi>.</seg></seg></p>

</div1>
